snippet.textDisplay:
Let's not forget that only one of these characters actually unleashed the power and caused the deaths of hundreds of thousands of people (and potentially, hundreds of millions more in the future). Or in his own words:

"We knew the world would not be the same. A few people laughed, a few people cried. Most people were silent. I remembered the line from the Hindu scripture, the Bhagavad Gita; Vishnu is trying to persuade the Prince that he should do his duty and, to impress him, takes on his multi-armed form and says, "Now I am become Death, the destroyer of worlds." I suppose we all thought that, one way or another."

Popular culture is great and fun and no one wants to be the buzzkill, but the impacts of one of these characters was very, very real and destructive. And it still is. We must remember the dangers of the power we hold in our hands.
